  • Add Course Description (1)
    Course IDCourse Description Location Timestamp
    15347 An introduction to the history,theory, graphics, and process of landscape design enabling students to begin designing landscapes that are functional, artistic, sustainable, water-wise,and beautiful. Students will learn the elements and principles of design as applied to landscape architecture and design, how to draw and color rend hand graphics using scale, and the steps of the design process. This course is an exploratory class for all majors who may elect landscape design, construction,or maintenance as a career and is a pre-requisite for higher level landscape design and construction courses. course-description\main.js 2018-06-15T15:45:45-06:00
